line_1: For her the never-dying myrtle weaves
line_2: A verdant chaplet of her odorous leaves;

line_1: SPRING's dewy hand on this fair summit weaves
line_2: And shades the beechen slopes with tender leaves,

line_1: With skilful hands, fair Hannah weaves,
First a new bark its silken tissue weaves,
line_2: New buds emerging widen into leaves;

line_1: With Paper-flags a floating cradle weaves,
line_2: And hides the smiling boy in Lotus-leaves;

line_1: While here and there an ashling weaves

line_2: And winds his web about the rivell'd leaves;
